00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:59,560
Whereas the next most complex would be methyl acetylene, and this particular molecule would

107
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:05,240
be called a terminal alkyne, because one side of the triple bond is continued by another

108
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:10,720
R group or another bond to carbon, whereas one end of it is terminated and capped off

109
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:13,800
by that hydrogen.

